news.title: Homebuyers can seek refund if possession offered without amenities: NCDRC
news.para: In order to meet the completion deadline and to avoid litigation, the builders' entire focus is on completing the construction of the flats and to offer possession but in most of the cases they do not put in place amenities like club, gym, green area etc at the time of handing over the flats.

news.title: Prestige Estates launches QIP to raise up to Rs 5,000 crore
news.para: Realty firm Prestige Estates Projects Ltd has launched a plan to raise up to Rs 5,000 crore through a Qualified Institutional Placement (QIP). The floor price for the equity shares has been set at Rs 1,755.09 per share. Recently, the company reported a 13% decline in net profit for the June quarter due to higher expenses.

news.title: Jio Finance in advanced stages of launching home loans
news.para: the company's MD and CEO Hitesh Sethia said, "We are also in advanced stages of launching Home Loans, which have been rolled out in Beta mode, and other products such as Loan Against Property and Loan on Securities are in the pipeline"

news.title: IBM renews lease for 8.3 lakh sq ft office space in Bengaluru
news.para: IBM has renewed a major lease for 830,000 square feet at Embassy Golf Links Business Park in Bengaluru, with an annual rental of ₹143 crore. This long-term agreement, one of the year's largest office transactions, includes a 10-year term with escalating rent provisions.

news.title: Clear Bridge Ventures acquires IT Park and two-acre land for Rs 335 crore in Mumbai
news.para: Clear Bridge Ventures has acquired an IT park in Malad, Mumbai for Rs 335 crore from Property Ventures (India). The property, developed in 2002, includes a land parcel, parking slots, and over 147,000 sq ft of saleable area. This transaction highlights the growing demand for office spaces in India’s commercial hubs.

news.title: Karan Johar leases duplex in Mumbai’s Pali Hill with total rent of Rs 3.06 crore
news.para: The monthly rent for the apartment in Pali Hill’s Union Park will start at Rs 8.10 lakh and increase to Rs 8.93 lakh by the third year. The total cost over 36 months will exceed Rs 3.06 crore. This mirrors the strong demand for luxury rentals in the city's prime locations.

news.title: Delhi: DDA signs MoU for drone surveys to combat land encroachments
news.para: Lieutenant Governor VK Saxena was shown the results of a trial run conducted over an area of 50 square kilometres. The results were encouraging, with high-resolution images being mapped clearly by the drones, it said.

news.title: China's Country Garden delays 2023 annual results again
news.para: Country Garden had previously delayed the results in March, saying it needed more time to collect information for making appropriate accounting estimates and judgements.

news.title: China Vanke posts losses of $1.4 billion in H1 2024
news.para: The setbacks make Vanke the latest Chinese developer to be caught up in a mounting crisis within the real estate sector, following Evergrande and Country Garden.

news.title: China's mortgage loans fall, property development loans rise in June 2024
news.para: China's outstanding individual mortgage loans totalled 37.79 trillion yuan ($5.33 trillion) at the end of June, down 2.1% from a year earlier, the People's Bank of China said.

news.title: Max Estates plans to raise Rs 800 crore through QIP
news.para: The panel also approved the floor price for the issue at Rs 628.74 per equity share.

news.title: Uttarakhand: Khurpia farm to be set up as smart industrial city
news.para: Khurpia farm in Uttarakhand's Kichha will be turned into a smart industrial city under the Amritsar-Kolkata industrial corridor, with a Rs 6,180 crore investment. Covering 1,002 acres, it is expected to create 75,000 jobs. The industrial hub will focus on automobile, engineering, and fabrication sectors.

news.title: Fletcher Building to resolve leaky pipes issue in Western Australia homes
news.para: Last year, Fletcher had said that nearly 1,500 of the 15,000 houses constructed in Western Australia (WA) using Iplex's pipes had faced plumbing failures between mid-2017 and mid-2022.

news.title: House prices dip marginally in UK in August 2024
news.para: In annual terms, prices were 2.4% higher than in August last year, the fastest increase since December 2022 - shortly after the "mini-budget" crisis that pushed up borrowing costs - but a smaller gain than the median forecast of 2.9% in the poll.

news.title: WeWork India in talks to lease 400,000 sq ft in Delhi, Gurugram
news.para: The company is taking 148,000 at Prestige Trade Tower and 115,000 at Bharti Worldmark 6 at Delhi’s Aerocity, besides 140,000 at DLF’sCyber City in Gurgaon.

news.title: China's Kaisa posts 36.3% increase in losses in H1 2024
news.para: Chinese property developer Kaisa posted on Thursday a 36.3 percent increase in losses, highlighting the persistent challenges faced by real estate firms as home sales decline in a slowing economy. Losses increased by 36.3 percent compared to the same period last year, when it totalled 6.6 billion yuan ($930 million).

news.title: Goa: Construction permissions continue to be granted based on earlier ODPs & RP 2021
news.para: TCP chief town planner Rajesh Naik said that in the absence of any applicable statutory provisions, the same ODP or development plan which was in force in “affected planning areas” on the date of its withdrawal shall continue to apply.

news.title: Formulate plans to make Amaravati into AI city: Andhra Pradesh CM
news.para: Andhra Pradesh Chief Minister N Chandrababu Naidu has directed officials to develop Amaravati into an Artificial Intelligence city. He emphasized the swift completion of government buildings and revival of the HappyNest project. Naidu also called for the speedy implementation of Metro rail projects in Vijayawada and Visakhapatnam.

news.title: Hosur metro extension faces final hurdles
news.para: The study, conducted by Balaji Rail Road Systems, is nearly complete. CMRL has sought the assistance of BMRCL to finalise the report.

news.title: Ulhasnagar civic body to demolish 16-floor illegal building
news.para: This includes a 120-foot DP road on the front side and an 80-foot DP road on the other side. In such a situation, although UMC has asked the developer to demolish the illegal portion of the building, technically, the entire structure will have to be demolished.
